# RESONANCE BRIDGE — environment template
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. The real .env is gitignored and NEVER committed.
# RULE: keys go straight from the provider dashboard into your .env by your
# own hands. Never paste a real key into any chat — with any AI, ever.
# If one ever leaks anywhere, rotate it at the dashboard immediately.

# ── PHASE 1 (local Grammar) — NO KEYS REQUIRED ─────────────────────
# knowledge.db path only; not secret, but configurable:
KNOWLEDGE_DB_PATH=C:/_superposition/resonance-knowledge/knowledge.db

# ── PHASE 2 (Supabase: Superposition + resonance-knowledge cloud) ──
# From: Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API
# Use the ANON key (read-only ward); avoid the service_role key unless a
# consent-gated write tool explicitly requires it.
SUPABASE_URL_KNOWLEDGE=
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY_KNOWLEDGE=
SUPABASE_URL_SUPERPOSITION=
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY_SUPERPOSITION=
# ── PHASE 2.5 (platform lines — the audhdities.com switchboard) ────
# Least privilege everywhere: name every key `bridge-<service>` at the
# dashboard so its provenance is visible; store each in the password manager.

# GitHub: github.com → Settings → Developer settings →
#   Fine-grained personal access tokens → Generate new.
#   Repository access: ONLY the repos the Bridge serves (AudHDities, resonance-*).
#   Permissions: Contents R/W, Pull requests R/W, Metadata R. 90-day expiry.
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# Vercel: vercel.com → Account Settings → Tokens → Create.
#   Scope to the account/team that owns audhdities.com; set an expiry.
VERCEL_TOKEN=

# Resend: resend.com → API Keys → Create.
#   Permission: "Sending access" only (not Full access) until a tool needs more.
RESEND_API_KEY=

# Stripe: dashboard.stripe.com → Developers → API keys →
#   "Create restricted key" — READ-ONLY on what we query (Charges, Customers,
#   Products). NEVER put the full live secret key here. Test-mode first.
STRIPE_RESTRICTED_KEY=

# ── PHASE 2.5 — AIRTABLE (the memory line: KP's prior organizations) ──
# Holds: earlier attempts at organizing the chaos, the song portfolio,
# the music column's photography. READ-ONLY by scope design.
# From: airtable.com/create/tokens → "Create new token"
#   Name: bridge-airtable (provenance visible at the dashboard)
#   Scopes: data.records:read + schema.bases:read — NOTHING else
#   Access: only the bases the Bridge should see (add per base, deliberately)
AIRTABLE_API_KEY=

# ── PHASE 2.5 — BLIZZARD / BATTLE.NET (the Azeroth residence records) ──
# Recovers what the thin export withheld: character roster echoes,
# ACHIEVEMENT TIMESTAMPS (the dated activity record of the WoW lifetime),
# mounts/pets/titles. No /played hours — Blizzard keeps the odometer in-game.
# From: develop.battle.net → "API Access" → Create Client (free)
#   Name: bridge-blizzard · Redirect URL: none needed for our use
#   Client-credentials token reaches all PUBLIC character-profile endpoints
#   (character + achievements + collections by realm/name). Account-level
#   roster would need user OAuth — skip unless wanted later.
BLIZZARD_CLIENT_ID=
BLIZZARD_CLIENT_SECRET=

# ── PHASE 3 (service lines) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Kimi / Moonshot (pro): platform.moonshot.ai → API Keys
# First test per the Weaver's directive: bridge the Library's gaps.
MOONSHOT_API_KEY=

# Leonardo + DaVinci: LINES CLOSED 2026-07-04 (Weaver's finding) — neither
# offers a task API; automating them would need browser-driving agents.
# Revisit only if their platforms ship real APIs. The DaVinci trial clock
# is therefore moot.

# ── PHASE 4 (Aethelred's local line) ───────────────────────────────
# Local only when the Alienware home stands; no cloud key. Placeholder:
AETHELRED_LOCAL_URL=http://localhost:11434
